title: $:/plugins/rimir/namespace/readme

! Namespace

Namespace-aware link resolution for TiddlyWiki. Replaces the core
{{{ [[…]] }}} parser rule so link targets are resolved relative to the
source tiddler's own title prefix.

!! What it does (stage 1)

A link {{{ [[REF]] }}} is resolved in this order:

# ''Literal'' — if a tiddler titled exactly `REF` exists, use it.
  ''~$:/…'' system links always match here.
# ''Absolute'' — if `REF` contains a slash, it is treated as a full title.
# ''Walk-up'' — walk up the source tiddler's title prefix:
  from //source// `a/b/c/d/X`, try `a/b/c/d/REF`, `a/b/c/REF`,
  `a/b/REF`, `a/REF`, `REF`. First hit wins.
# ''Unresolved'' — rendered with the `ns-unresolved` class
  (wavy underline + ⚠ marker) and a tooltip listing the candidates tried.

Example: a tiddler titled `a/b/OWASP/ASVS/4.0.3/docs/intro` can simply
write {{{ [[V3.3]] }}} to refer to `a/b/OWASP/ASVS/4.0.3/V3.3` — no
need to spell out the full path.

!! How it works

The wikirule converts {{{ [[REF]] }}} into:

```
<$let __nsref__="REF">
  <$link to={{{ [<__nsref__>ns-resolve<currentTiddler>] }}}
         class={{{ [<__nsref__>ns-resolve-class<currentTiddler>] }}}>
    text
  </$link>
</$let>
```

Resolution happens at render time via the `ns-resolve` filter operator,
so references still resolve correctly under transclusion (they follow
the widget's `currentTiddler`, not the source tiddler of the text).

!! Deferred

Later stages will add:

* `_latest` pseudo-segment (version-max resolution)
* `\context` pragma, `<$context>` widget, and `context:` field overrides
* Named aliases (and pattern aliases) for short cross-context shortcuts
* Mount points / namespace root anchoring
* Backlink indexer integration (so core search / relink see resolved targets)
* Parallel treatment for transclusion {{{ {{…}} }}}

!! Limitations of stage 1

* Core TiddlyWiki's backlink index and the `relink` plugin only see the
  literal `[[REF]]` string, not the resolved target. Backlinks from
  walk-up-resolved references are therefore missing until stage 6 lands.
* No configuration UI yet.
